# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Market Gap Finder — environment variables
#
# ALL of these are OPTIONAL. With none set, the app runs end-to-end on
# realistic mock fixtures and labels each source "mock" in the UI. Add real
# credentials to promote a source to "live".
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Reddit (demand / pain signal) ---------------------------------------
# NO APP REQUIRED: with no credentials the adapter does *keyless* research —
# Reddit's public search.json blended with DuckDuckGo site:reddit.com discovery,
# under a strict request budget (stops on 429, caches results). Reddit may block
# unauthenticated requests from some IPs (403), in which case it degrades to mock
# and says so in the UI. For higher, more reliable limits, add an OAuth app
# (type: "script" at https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps):
# REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
# REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
# REDDIT_USER_AGENT=market-gap-finder/0.1 (by u/yourname)
#
# Keyless tuning (optional):
# REDDIT_USE_WEB_SEARCH=1        # blend DuckDuckGo discovery (set 0 to disable)

# --- arXiv (research momentum) -------------------------------------------
# No key required.

# --- Hacker News (demand + tech momentum) --------------------------------
# No key required — keyless Algolia API (Ask HN = demand, Show HN = supply,
# high-point stories = momentum).

# --- GitHub trending (capability tailwind) -------------------------------
# Works keyless (low rate limit, cached hard). Add a token for higher limits:
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# --- Newsletters (curated "what's new" via RSS) --------------------------
# Uses a built-in default feed list (TLDR, Ben's Bites, Pragmatic Engineer,
# Import AI, Simon Willison, a16z, Lenny's). Override with a comma-separated list:
# NEWSLETTER_FEEDS=https://tldr.tech/api/rss/tech,https://importai.substack.com/feed

# --- LLM ------------------------------------------------------------------
# By default the synthesis step uses your Claude *subscription* via the local
# Claude Code login (agent-sdk -> cli), so NO key is needed. Set a key only if
# you want to bill the Anthropic API instead.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
#
# Force a backend: agent-sdk | cli | api | fixture  (default: auto)
# LLM_BACKEND=
# LLM_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
# CLAUDE_CLI_PATH=claude

# --- Cache ----------------------------------------------------------------
# CACHE_PATH=cache.db
